<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>If you set the columns of a query right after instantiating a Zend_Db_Table_Select object it will select both table.* and table.fooColumn.</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$select = $table-&gt;select()-&gt;columns('product_id');
</code></pre>

<p>This generates a query similar to this one:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
SELECT zfproducts.*, zfproducts.product_id FROM zfproducts
</code></pre>

<p>While this should be</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
SELECT zfproducts.product_id FROM zfproducts
</code></pre>

